==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ine-pro|grc}} {{m|ine-pro|*ḱwṓ}}. Cognates include Latin {{m|la|canis}}, Sanskrit {{m|sa|श्वन्|tr=śván}} and Old English {{m|ang|hund}} (English {{m|en|hound}}). The final {{m|grc||-ν}} in the nominative singular which was absent in {{m|ine-pro|*ḱwṓ}} was restored in Greek by analogy to other forms in the paradigm.

